The '''Ford Crestline Skyliner''' is an automobile that was built by [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] featuring a [[hardtop|2 door hardtop]] body style with an integrated [[acrylic glass]] panel over the front seating area.<ref>[http://www.oldcarbrochures.com/main.php?g2_itemId=42448&g2_imageViewsIndex=1 The 1954 Ford brochure, pages 4&5]{{Dead link|date=December 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Retrieved on 5 January 2010</ref> Part of the [[Ford Crestline|1954 American Ford Crestline range]], it boasted a "freshness of view" through the green-tinted panel. 13,144 were sold in the single year of production, more than the two years of [[Ford Crown Victoria Skyliner|Crown Victoria Skyliner]] production that would follow.

[[Mercury (automobile)|Mercury]]'s [[Mercury Monterey|Monterey]] '''Sun Valley''' was similar. 9,761 were built in 1954.
